    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and put in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>garlic French fries</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-pork-memphis-style-philly-with-garlic-french-sweet-potato-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer your<strong> BBQ pulled pork</strong> and any juices to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Cover with<strong> tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 30 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-pork-memphis-style-philly-with-garlic-french-sweet-potato-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-pork-memphis-style-philly-with-garlic-french-sweet-potato-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> <strong>strips </strong>with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 10-12 min or until golden and softened \u2013 this is your <strong>caramelised onion & pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-pork-memphis-style-philly-with-garlic-french-sweet-potato-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Cut a slit into the top of your <strong>hot dog bun[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-pork-memphis-style-philly-with-garlic-french-sweet-potato-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After 30 min, remove the dish with the pulled pork from the oven and discard the<strong> tin foil</strong></p><p>Pull the <strong>BBQ pulled pork</strong> apart using two forks</p><p>Add your <strong>BBQ sauce</strong> to the pulled pork and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>BBQ pulled pork filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-pork-memphis-style-philly-with-garlic-french-sweet-potato-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>BBQ pulled pork filling</strong> between the<strong> bun[s]</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>caramelised onion & pepper </strong>and <strong>grated cheese</strong>, then add to a baking tray (or two!) and put in the oven for 5-6 min or until the cheese has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>pulled pork Memphis-style Philly</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-pork-memphis-style-philly-with-garlic-french-sweet-potato-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pulled pork Memphis-style Philly </strong>with the <strong>garlic French fries </strong>and a dollop of your <strong>tomato ketchup</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
